# AWS Free-Tier DevOps Project — Complete Step-by-Step Guide

**Stack:** Node.js (Express) · AWS EC2 · S3 · API Gateway (optional) · IAM · Security Groups · GitHub Actions · CloudWatch · k6

---

## 0. Architecture Overview

```
                    ┌─────────────────────┐
   Internet ───────▶│  Security Group      │
                    │  (80/443/22 only)    │
                    └──────────┬───────────┘
                               │
                    ┌──────────▼───────────┐
                    │   EC2 (t2.micro)     │
                    │  ┌─────────────────┐ │        ┌──────────────┐
                    │  │ Nginx (reverse  │ │        │  CloudWatch  │
                    │  │ proxy + TLS)    │ │───────▶│  Agent →     │
                    │  └────────┬────────┘ │        │  Logs/Metrics│
                    │  ┌────────▼────────┐ │        └──────────────┘
                    │  │ Node.js/Express │ │
                    │  │ (PM2 process)   │ │
                    │  └────────┬────────┘ │
                    └───────────┼───────────┘
                                │
                       ┌────────▼────────┐
                       │   Amazon S3     │
                       │ (assets/backups)│
                       └─────────────────┘

  GitHub ──push to main──▶ GitHub Actions ──SSH deploy──▶ EC2
  (Optional) API Gateway ──HTTP proxy──▶ EC2 (for rate limiting / API key mgmt)
  IAM Role attached to EC2 → grants least-privilege access to S3/CloudWatch
```

Use this as the basis for your "architecture diagram" deliverable — recreate it in draw.io, Lucidchart, or the AWS free diagramming tool ([app.diagrams.net](https://app.diagrams.net)) using official AWS icons for the final report.

