## Part 2 — Networking: VPC & Security Groups

Free tier gives you a **default VPC** already — you don't need to create one from scratch.

### 2.1 Create a Security Group
1. **EC2** → **Security Groups** → **Create security group**.
2. Name: `app-sg`. Description: "Web app security group".
3. VPC: default.
4. **Inbound rules:**
   | Type | Port | Source | Purpose |
   |---|---|---|---|
   | SSH | 22 | *Your IP only* (`My IP`) | Admin access |
   | HTTP | 80 | 0.0.0.0/0 | Public web traffic |
   | HTTPS | 443 | 0.0.0.0/0 | Encrypted web traffic |
5. **Outbound rules:** leave default (all traffic allowed) — the app needs to reach npm registry, S3, CloudWatch.

This satisfies "Configure Security Groups and firewall rules" with least-privilege SSH access.

