## Part 3 — Launch and Configure EC2

1. **EC2** → **Launch instance**.
2. Name: `app-server`.
3. AMI: **Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS** (free tier eligible).
4. Instance type: **t2.micro** (free tier).
5. Key pair: create new → `app-key.pem` → **download and keep it safe** (you cannot re-download).
6. Network settings: select your default VPC, **attach `app-sg`** security group created above.
7. Storage: 8–20 GB gp3 (free tier covers up to 30 GB).
8. **Advanced details** → IAM instance profile → select `EC2-App-Role`.
9. Launch instance.

### 3.1 Connect and set up the server
```bash
chmod 400 app-key.pem
ssh -i app-key.pem ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>
```

Install Node.js, PM2, Nginx, and the CloudWatch Agent:
```bash
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Node.js 20.x
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs git nginx

# Install PM2 (process manager, keeps app alive & restarts on crash)
sudo npm install -g pm2
pm2 startup systemd -u ubuntu --hp /home/ubuntu
# (run the command it prints, prefixed with sudo)
```

