## Part 8 — CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)

The workflow file is at `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` in this project. It:
1. Runs on every push to `main`.
2. Installs dependencies and does a basic sanity check.
3. SSHes into EC2, pulls the latest code, reinstalls dependencies, and restarts the app via PM2.

### 8.1 Add GitHub Secrets
Repo → **Settings** → **Secrets and variables** → **Actions** → **New repository secret**:
| Secret | Value |
|---|---|
| `EC2_HOST` | Your EC2 public IP |
| `EC2_USER` | `ubuntu` |
| `EC2_SSH_KEY` | Contents of your `app-key.pem` file |
| `S3_BUCKET_NAME` | Your bucket name |
| `AWS_REGION` | e.g. `ap-south-1` |

### 8.2 First-time EC2 prep for git-based deploys
```bash
mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/app
cd /home/ubuntu/app
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/<your-repo>.git .
```

Now every `git push origin main` will auto-deploy. Take a screenshot of a successful GitHub Actions run for your deliverables.

