## Part 9 — CloudWatch Monitoring, Dashboards & Alarms

### 9.1 Install & configure the CloudWatch Agent on EC2
```bash
wget https://s3.amazonaws.com/amazoncloudwatch-agent/ubuntu/amd64/latest/amazon-cloudwatch-agent.deb
sudo dpkg -i amazon-cloudwatch-agent.deb

sudo tee /opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/etc/config.json <<'EOF'
{
  "agent": { "metrics_collection_interval": 60, "run_as_user": "root" },
  "logs": {
    "logs_collected": {
      "files": {
        "collect_list": [
          {
            "file_path": "/home/ubuntu/app/app/logs/app.log",
            "log_group_name": "/app/access-logs",
            "log_stream_name": "{instance_id}"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  },
  "metrics": {
    "namespace": "CustomAppMetrics",
    "metrics_collected": {
      "mem": { "measurement": ["mem_used_percent"] },
      "disk": { "measurement": ["used_percent"], "resources": ["/"] },
      "cpu": { "measurement": ["cpu_usage_idle", "cpu_usage_user"], "totalcpu": true }
    }
  }
}
EOF

sudo /opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/bin/amazon-cloudwatch-agent-ctl \
  -a fetch-config -m ec2 -s \
  -c file:/opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/etc/config.json
```
This collects **application logs** (satisfies "Collect application logs") plus memory/disk/CPU custom metrics.

### 9.2 Build a Dashboard
1. **CloudWatch** → **Dashboards** → **Create dashboard** → name `AppMonitoring`.
2. Add widgets:
   - EC2 `CPUUtilization` (built-in, no agent needed)
   - `NetworkIn` / `NetworkOut`
   - Custom `mem_used_percent`, `disk_used_percent` (from agent)
   - Log widget showing recent lines from `/app/access-logs`

### 9.3 Create Alarms
1. **CloudWatch** → **Alarms** → **Create alarm**.
2. Metric: EC2 → `CPUUtilization` → threshold **> 70% for 5 minutes**.
3. Notification: create an **SNS topic**, subscribe your email.
4. Repeat for a `StatusCheckFailed` alarm (instance health) and optionally a high-memory alarm using the custom metric.

Take screenshots of the dashboard and a triggered/test alarm for your deliverables.

