## Part 11 — Analyze Bottlenecks & Suggest Optimizations

In your final report, structure this section as:

| Observation | Likely Cause | Suggested Optimization |
|---|---|---|
| p95 latency spikes above ~50 concurrent users | Single t2.micro vCPU saturated, Node.js is single-threaded | Use PM2 cluster mode (`pm2 start server.js -i max`) to use all vCPUs; consider a larger instance or Auto Scaling Group |
| CPU hits 100% during `/api/compute` calls | Synchronous CPU-bound loop blocks the event loop | Offload heavy computation to a worker thread or separate microservice |
| Error rate rises during traffic spikes | No load balancing / single point of failure | Add an Application Load Balancer + Auto Scaling Group across 2+ instances |
| High latency variability | T2 burstable CPU credits exhausted | Monitor `CPUCreditBalance` metric; move to `t3` or non-burstable type under sustained load |
| Disk I/O during logging | Synchronous file writes | Use async logging / ship logs directly via CloudWatch Agent instead of writing to disk first |

Tailor this table to what you *actually observe* in your own k6 run + CloudWatch data — reviewers will expect real numbers, not just theory.

